snippet.textDisplay: I've always liked Ali Zafar's voice and he was great but Sara Haider's voice is shiver-inducingly beautiful. I'm glad she got the chance to be in the spotlight. I've never been fond of remixes that just take a song and randomly make it faster/add new beats with no care, but this is an actual re-imagining of a song that was already lovely to make it enjoyable in a whole different way and I loved the vocals and the instrumental parts. Well done everyone involved!
